description.narrative:
The goal of the project is to reduce corruption risks in public property management in Ukraine. 
The goal will be achieved through:
The establishment of an effective IT system for accounting of the national and municipal property; launch the civic oversight of lease and privatization procedures, including via Prozorro.Sale; legislative changes to minimize corruption risks, prevent violations and ensure fair rules for all the stakeholders engaged.
In order to achieve the goal of the project, TI Ukraine puts forward following specific outcomes:
- Transparent, accessible and open market and improvement of selling and leasing procedures of national and municipal assets through implementation of technical development of ETS Prozorro.Sale;
- equal passive access to information about public property management;
- Launched civic oversight of national and municipal property management through establishing a regional civic network;
- Improved legislative framework of public property realization through advocacy on national and municipal level.

Transparency International Ukraine (TIU) has submitted an application to the Swedish Embassy for a support of 13,5 million Swedish Crowns for a project to support the development of the state-owned procurement system “Prozorro.Sale”. Prozorro.Sale is an open platform that allows state organizations to sell, rent, lease and give concessions on public property. The system has been shown to be effective and has contributed to reduced corruption. The Swedish support will be catalytic and support the further development of the system with new functionality as well as supporting a migration of the system to domestic severs as required by Ukrainian legislation. Apart from the technical support TIU will develop additional systems for monitoring and oversight of private and state users to improve functionality and reduce corruption. 
The goal of the project is to reduce corruption risks in public property management in Ukraine. 

The goal will be achieved through: - a) establishment of an effective IT system for accounting of the national and municipal property; - b) launch the civic oversight of lease and privatization procedures, including via Prozorro.Sale; - c) legislative changes to minimize corruption risks, prevent violations and ensure fair rules for all the stakeholders engaged. 

In order to achieve the goal of the project, TI Ukraine puts forward following specific outcomes: 

1. Transparent, accessible and open market and improvement of selling and leasing procedures of national and municipal assets through implementation of technical development of Prozorro.Sale;
2. Provided equal passive access to information about public property management; 
3. Launched civic oversight of national and municipal property management through establishing a regional civic network;
4. Improved legislative framework of public property realization through advocacy on national and municipal level.

The embassy also envisages this contribution to lead to increased economic activity amongst local SMEs and that it will also contribute to municipal revenue.
